  "prompt_text": "Solve: If 3x + 2y = 12 and x - y = 1, find x and y. Show your work.",
  "response_text": "To solve the system of equations, we can use the method of substitution or elimination. In this case, we'll use the elimination method.\n\nGiven equations:\n1) 3x + 2y = 12\n2) x - y = 1\n\nFirst, we'll solve equation (2) for x:\nx = 1 + y\n\nNow, substitute x in equation (1):\n3(1 + y) + 2y = 12\n\nExpand the equation:\n3 + 3y + 2y = 12\n\nCombine like terms:\n5y + 3 = 12\n\nSubtract 3 from both sides:\n5y = 9\n\nDivide both sides by 5:\ny = 9/5\ny = 1.8\n\nNow that we have the value of y, substitute it back into equation (2) to find x:\nx - 1.8 = 1\n\nAdd 1.8 to both sides:\nx = 2.8\n\nTherefore, the values of x and y are x = 2.8 and y = 1.8.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 8\nY (Affective Modeling): 6\nF (Flexibility): 7\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
